Q: A rectangular piece of 150 sq m has a length which is 1m more than the 4 times the breadth. What is the perimeter of the piece?
Options: (a) 60 m (b) 61 m (c) 62 m (d) 63 m (e) 64 m
A:
 Let the breadth of the piece be x. Then the length of the piece = 4x + 1. Area of the piece = 150 sq m = x(4x + 1) = 150 x = 37.5 m. Perimeter of the piece = 2(4x + 1) + 2x = 2(4*37.5 + 1) = 300 m. So the answer is (d).

