Q: By himself, Jack can clean a yacht in 12 hours. On a particular day, he happens to finish two-thirds of the work. The remaining portion of the work is done by Jill, whose rate of cleaning is just 5% of what Jack can do. How long does it take Jill to finish the remaining work?
Options: (a) 4 (b) 8 (c) 22 (d) 50 (e) 20
A:
 Jack can clean a yacht in 12 hours. So he can clean 1/12 of the yacht in 1 hour. So he can clean 2/3 of the yacht in 2/3*12 = 8 hours. Jill's rate of cleaning is just 5% of what Jack can do. So Jill can clean 1/20 of the yacht in 1 hour. So Jill can clean 1/3 of the yacht in 1/3*20 = 6.67 hours. So the answer is (a).

