Q: Two cars are travelling from the same starting point in the same direction, having started their commute at the same time. The first car travels at a steady rate of 55 mph, while the second travels at a steady rate of 52 mph. How much time will pass before the cars are 15 miles away from each other?
Options: (a) 3 hours (b) 5 hours (c) 6 hours (d) 4 hours (e) 7 hours
A:
 The distance between the two cars after t hours is 55t - 52t = 3t. The cars are 15 miles away from each other when 3t = 15 --> t = 5. So the answer is (b).

